# Accessibility

## Semantic HTML

Use the correct element for the job:

```tsx
// BAD
<div onClick={handleClick}>Submit</div>
<div className="nav">...</div>

// GOOD
<button onClick={handleClick}>Submit</button>
<nav>...</nav>
```

Use `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<header>`, `<footer>` where appropriate.

## Keyboard Navigation

- All interactive elements (buttons, links, modals, dropdowns) must be operable with Tab, Enter, and Escape.
- Modals must trap focus inside and return focus to the trigger element on close.

## Contrast

Minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio for normal text, 3:1 for large text (18px+ bold or 24px+ regular). Use `text-foreground` on `bg-background` and `text-primary-foreground` on `bg-primary`.

## Icon Buttons

Icon-only buttons must have `aria-label`:

```tsx
<button aria-label="Close menu" onClick={onClose}>
  <XIcon className="h-5 w-5" />
</button>
```

## Images and Headings

- Content images: descriptive `alt` text. Decorative: `alt="" aria-hidden="true"`.
- One h1 per page. Sequential levels (h1 → h2 → h3). Never skip levels.
